First Lady Melania Trump gave a speech at Joint Base Andrews, expressing her gratitude for military personnel and their families. She spent the day with the children of service members and thanked everyone who made it possible. Melania stated that every child with a parent in the military should be proud because their parent is a true American hero. She praised the Air Force for their response to the recent hurricanes in Texas and Florida, saying that they have made America proud. Melania also thanked the families of service members for their sacrifices and assured them that the administration will always support the United States Air Force.